com.example.bettertrialbook.models

Class Geolocation

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.example.bettertrialbook.models.Geolocation
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    android.os.Parcelable, java.lang.Comparable<Geolocation>

    public class Geolocation
extends java.lang.Object
implements android.os.Parcelable, java.lang.Comparable<Geolocation>
    Geolocation class stores a location object containing the lat and lon of the trial's geolocation. We chose to create a Geolocation class so that if we ever need to add more attributes aside from location to a Geolocation, the structure for doing so is already implemented. The class implements Parcelable so that it can be easily passed through intents between activities. It implements Comparable for easy comparisons with itself.
